      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HATARI (8) is a consistent type who is new to this track. Strong winner last time by 4 lengths at Ballarat in Grade 4/5 in the quickest time on the program (25.06). Comes through a solid form race last start. Expected to be right there at the finish again. SHE LIKES BEER (1) stalked the pace from a low draw last start and fought on well to finish 0.8 lengths away in second (25.22) at this track in a Grade 4/5 over 450m. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Expected to feature again. NEEDFUL (2) has an excellent record over this course and distance having never missed the placings in five starts, including two wins and three placings. Missed the frame latest (23.71) when sixth over 410m at Horsham in a Grade 5. Can hit the frame with the right run. FLAMING SMOOTH (4) has strong claims after a top-three finish last time out.",
